---
import { POLICY_FILE_URL, POLICY_DOCS_URL, POLICY_REPO } from '../data/plugins';
---
<aside class="policy-banner">
  <div class="policy-banner__icon" aria-hidden="true">🛡️</div>
  <div class="policy-banner__body">
    <strong>Global APM policy in force.</strong>
    Every Zava repo automatically inherits
    <a href={POLICY_FILE_URL} rel="noopener"><code>{POLICY_REPO}/apm-policy.yml</code></a>
    via the <code>.github</code> default-config pattern.
    CI runs <code>apm audit --ci</code> on every PR and merges are blocked on
    policy violation.
    <br />
    Learn how it's wired up in the
    <a href={POLICY_DOCS_URL} rel="noopener">APM CI policy setup guide</a>.
  </div>
</aside>

<style>
  .policy-banner {
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.85rem;
    align-items: flex-start;
    padding: 0.85rem 1rem;
    border-radius: 12px;
    border: 1px solid #d8b95b;
    background: #fff7d6;
    color: #4a3705;
    margin: 1rem 0 1.5rem;
    font-size: 0.92rem;
    line-height: 1.45;
  }
  .policy-banner code { background: rgba(0,0,0,.06); padding: 0 .25em; border-radius: 4px; }
  .policy-banner a { color: #5b3a00; text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 2px; }
  .policy-banner__icon { font-size: 1.4rem; line-height: 1; padding-top: 2px; }
  :root[data-theme='dark'] .policy-banner {
    background: #2d2104;
    color: #fde68a;
    border-color: #a07c1a;
  }
  :root[data-theme='dark'] .policy-banner a { color: #fcd34d; }
</style>
